{"parentUuid":"09a72453-55cd-4107-bf33-09f0c831b77c","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_011Ccwoy2UdjUDGJJLEfjJYa","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_016xWJZrAaTjqLc2gMoNMvMG","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"./incident.html","content":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Incident Report</title>\n    <style>\n        * {\n            margin: 0;\n            padding: 0;\n            box-sizing: border-box;\n        }\n\n        body {\n            font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', 'Roboto', 'Oxygen', 'Ubuntu', 'Cantarell', sans-serif;\n            line-height: 1.6;\n            color: #333;\n            background-color: #f5f5f5;\n            padding: 20px;\n        }\n\n        .container {\n            max-width: 800px;\n            margin: 0 auto;\n            background-color: white;\n            border-radius: 8px;\n            box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);\n            padding: 40px;\n        }\n\n        h1 {\n            color: #d32f2f;\n            margin-bottom: 30px;\n            font-size: 2em;\n            border-bottom: 3px solid #d32f2f;\n            padding-bottom: 15px;\n        }\n\n        h2 {\n            color: #1976d2;\n            margin-top: 30px;\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\n            font-size: 1.3em;\n        }\n\n        .summary {\n            background-color: #fff3e0;\n            border-left: 4px solid #ff9800;\n            padding: 15px;\n            margin-bottom: 30px;\n            border-radius: 4px;\n        }\n\n        .summary p {\n            color: #e65100;\n            font-weight: 500;\n        }\n\n        ol, ul {\n            margin-left: 20px;\n            margin-bottom: 20px;\n        }\n\n        ol li, ul li {\n            margin-bottom: 12px;\n            padding-left: 8px;\n        }\n\n        .root-cause {\n            background-color: #f3e5f5;\n            border-left: 4px solid #9c27b0;\n            padding: 15px;\n            margin-bottom: 30px;\n            border-radius: 4px;\n        }\n\n        .root-cause p {\n            color: #6a1b9a;\n        }\n\n        .action-items {\n            background-color: #e8f5e9;\n            border-left: 4px solid #4caf50;\n            padding: 15px;\n            border-radius: 4px;\n        }\n\n        .action-items h3 {\n            color: #2e7d32;\n            margin-bottom: 12px;\n            font-size: 1em;\n        }\n\n        .action-item {\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\n            padding-left: 15px;\n        }\n\n        .action-item:last-child {\n            margin-bottom: 0;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <h1>Incident Report</h1>\n\n        <div class=\"summary\">\n            <p><strong>Summary:</strong> Checkout API returned 500s for 12 minutes due to a database connection pool exhaustion.</p>\n        </div>\n\n        <h2>Timeline</h2>\n        <ol>\n            <li><strong>14:02</strong> - Deploy of new connection pool configuration released to production</li>\n            <li><strong>14:10</strong> - Traffic spike observed, exceeding normal patterns by 45%</li>\n            <li><strong>14:12</strong> - Alerts fired for elevated error rates and response timeouts on Checkout API</li>\n            <li><strong>14:14</strong> - Database connection pool size reverted to previous stable configuration</li>\n            <li><strong>14:14</strong> - System recovered, error rates returned to baseline</li>\n        </ol>\n\n        <h2>Root Cause</h2>\n        <div class=\"root-cause\">\n            <p>The incident was caused by a deployment at 14:02 that reduced the database connection pool size from 100 to 50 connections as part of a cost optimization effort. This change, when combined with an unexpected traffic spike at 14:10, exhausted the available connections. The reduced pool was unable to handle the spike, resulting in connection timeouts and 500 errors on the Checkout API. The traffic spike was attributed to a promotional email campaign that was sent earlier than anticipated.</p>\n        </div>\n\n        <h2>Action Items</h2>\n        <div class=\"action-items\">\n            <div class=\"action-item\">\n                <h3>1. Implement automated load testing for pool configuration changes</h3>\n                <p>Before deploying any database connection pool modifications, conduct automated load testing simulating traffic spikes to ensure the new configuration can handle peak loads. Target completion: within 2 weeks.</p>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"action-item\">\n                <h3>2. Establish pre-deployment coordination with marketing team</h3>\n                <p>Create a process requiring marketing to notify the engineering team of any promotional campaigns that could drive significant traffic spikes. This ensures infrastructure scaling decisions are made with visibility into planned traffic events. Target completion: within 1 week.</p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8083,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":1761,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":8083,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":10,"output_tokens":1761,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8083,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":8083},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccwoy1pwgWyUv8yobbGon","type":"assistant","uuid":